title: Google Charges More than Twice Its Rivals in Ad Deals, Wins 80% of Its Own Auctions, Court Documents Say; Suit by state attorneys general cites Google's staff commenting on conflicts of interest: the ''analogy would be if Goldman or Citibank owned the NYSE'
text:
The unredacted filing on Friday in the U.S. District Court of the Southern District of New York came after a federal judge ruled last week that much of the antitrust suit could be unsealed.
